term: far-Western blotting evidence used in manual assertion

term: split-ubiquitin functional complementation evidence used in manual assertion

term: yeast one-hybrid evidence used in manual assertion

term: immunological assay evidence used in manual assertion

term: bait-prey hybrid interaction evidence used in manual assertion

term: protein binding evidence used in manual assertion

term: affinity evidence used in manual assertion

term: co-purification evidence used in manual assertion

term: immunofluorescence super resolution microscopy evidence used in manual assertion

term: immunofluorescence super resolution microscopy evidence

term: RNA-sequencing evidence used in automatic assertion

term: quantitative reverse transcription polymerase chain reaction evidence used in automatic assertion.

term: 3C-qPCR evidence
comment: A type of 3C evidence evidence that 1) quantifies interactions between a single pair of genomic loci (not multiple interactions) and 2) performs quantitative polymerase chain reaction (qPCR) in the quantitation step.

term: quantitative reverse transcription polymerase chain reaction evidence used in manual assertion
comment: A type of quantitative reverse transcription polymerase chain reaction evidence used in manual assertion.

term: Hi-C evidence
comment: A type of chromosome conformation-based evidence that is derived by performing immunoprecipitation enrichment of the biotin labelled ligated fragments events prior to sequencing of the library and mapping it to the genome.

term: 3C-seq evidence
comment: A type of chromosome conformation-based evidence that is derived by inverse polymerase chain reaction (inverse PCR) on a circularized 3C library prior to product quantitation with multiplexed high-throughput (HT) sequencing.

term: chromosome conformation-based evidence
comment: A type of experimental evidence that is based on a five-step technique of cross-linking DNA in vivo, restriction digestion, intramolecular ligation, reversing DNA cross-links, DNA processing, and quantitation that serves to analyze the spatial organization of chromatin in a cell and quantify the number of interactions between genomic loci that are nearby in 3-D space.

term: 3C evidence
comment: A type of chromosome conformation-based evidence that is derived by 1) quantifying interactions between a single pair of genomic loci and not multiple interactions and 2) performing polymerase chain reaction (PCR) in the final product quantitation step.

term: cell growth assay evidence
comment: A type of direct assay evidence where biological cell development, i.e. an increase in cell mass and size are measured.

term: 4C evidence
comment: A type of chromosome conformation-based evidence that is derived by inverse polymerase chain reaction (inverse PCR) on a prior circularized 3C library followed by product quantitation with a microarray.

term: quantitative reverse transcription polymerase chain reaction evidence
comment: A type of reverse transcription polymerase chain reaction evidence that combines reverse transcription polymerase chain reaction and real time polymerase chain reaction to quantitatively assay for the detection of RNA levels.

term: 5C evidence
comment: A type of chromosome conformation-based evidence that is derived by performing ligation-mediated amplification (LMA) prior to product quantitation.

term: cell-based assay evidence
comment: A type of direct assay evidence resulting from the study of cells.

term: single-cell RNA-sequencing evidence
comment: A type of RNA-sequencing evidence that uses a single cell as the source of the RNA.

term: chromatin immunoprecipitation-chip evidence
comment: A type of chromatin immunoprecipitation evidence that uses a tiling microarray for the detection of protein-bound DNA regions where chromatin is immunoprecipitated for protein tagging and DNA is sheared from the cross-linked protein-DNA complex to be arrayed revealing the protein-bound genomic regions.

term: ubiquitination assay evidence
comment: A type of direct assay evidence where ubiquitinated residues on a protein are detected.

term: quantitative polymerase chain reaction evidence
comment: A type of DNA detection assay evidence where the reaction product is quantified in real-time across cycles by means of fluorescent dyes or fluorescent probes for detection and quantification of specific sequences in a DNA sample.

term: translation assay evidence
comment: A type of direct assay evidence where de novo protein synthesis is detected.

term: chromatin immunoprecipitation-seq evidence
comment: A type of chromatin immunoprecipitation evidence that uses high-throughput sequencing where immunoprecipitated DNA fragments are funnelled into a massively parallel sequencer to produce multiple short reads for locating binding sites of DNA-associated proteins.

term: chain termination sequencing evidence
comment: A type of nucleotide sequencing assay in which DNA sequence is determined by addition of a primed DNA template to a reaction mixture, followed by addition of DNA polymerase, deoxynucleosidetriphosphates (dNTPs - one of which may be radiolabeled), and one of four di-deoxynucleotidetriphosphates (ddNTPs), after which DNA elongation is terminated and the DNA is separated by size and imaged.

term: polyADP-ribosylation assay evidence
comment: A type of direct assay evidence where ADP-ribosylated residues in proteins are detected.

term: chromatin immunoprecipitation evidence
comment: A type of immunoprecipitation evidence that is used to identify a protein binding site on a genomic DNA sequence.

term: phosphatase assay evidence
comment: A type of direct assay evidence where the removal of phosphatase groups from a protein is detected.

term: chromatin immunoprecipitation-PCR evidence
comment: A type of chromatin immunoprecipitation evidence that uses polymerase chain reaction (PCR) where specific primers are used on the pulled-down DNA for DNA detection.

term: sumoylation assay evidence
comment: A type of direct assay evidence where sumoylated residues on a protein are detected.

term: chromatin immunoprecipitation-qPCR evidence
comment: A type of chromatin immunoprecipitation evidence in which protein-DNA interactions are investigated at known genomic binding sites through a process of ChIP, DNA purification, and finally quantitative polymerase chain reaction (qPCR) for DNA detection.

term: protein kinase assay evidence
comment: A type of enzymatic activity assay evidence that measures transfer of a phosphate to a peptide or protein substrate by a protein kinase.

term: high throughput nucleotide sequencing assay evidence
comment: A type of nucleotide sequencing assay evidence in which a sequence is derived from a parallelized sequencing technique.

term: farnesylation assay evidence
comment: A type of direct assay evidence where farnesylated residues in proteins are detected.

term: Illumina sequencing evidence
comment: A type of high throughput nucleotide sequencing evidence in which sequence is determined through hybridization of adaptor-ligated DNA to a glass slide on which each fragment is simultaneously clonally amplified, followed by progressive rounds of base incorporation with fluorescently-tagged nucleotides, washing, imaging, and cleavage.

term: deubiquitination assay evidence
comment: A type of direct assay evidence where the removal of ubiquitin groups from a protein is detected.

term: 454 pyrosequencing evidence
comment: A type of high throughput nucleotide sequencing evidence in which the sequence for a ssDNA is determined by addition of primers and then nucleotides, one base pair at a time (which generate a specific fluorescence), to the target strand.

term: palmitoylation assay evidence
comment: A type of direct assay evidence where palmitoylated residues in a protein are detected.

term: SOLiD sequencing evidence
comment: A type of high throughput nucleotide sequencing evidence in which sequence is determined through rounds of ligation-based sequencing with fluorescently-labeled Di-base probes and cleavage, after which the template is reset, with a primer offset by one base, for subsequent rounds of ligation.

term: methylation assay evidence
comment: A type of direct assay evidence where methylated residues of a substarte (RNA/DNA or protein) are detected.

term: desumoylation assay evidence
comment: A type of direct assay evidence where the removal of sumo groups from a protein is detected.

term: sequencing assay evidence
comment: A type of experimental evidence where the order of molecules that constitute a biopolymer is determined.

term: demethylation assay evidence
comment: A type of direct assay evidence where the removal of methyl groups from a substrate (RNA/DNA or protein) is detected.

term: manual assertion
comment: An assertion method that involves human review.

term: nucleotide sequencing assay evidence
comment: A type of sequencing assay that determines the sequence of a biopolymer comprised of nucleotides.

term: defarnesylation assay evidence
comment: A type of direct assay evidence where the removal of farnesyl groups from a protein is detected.

term: biological aspect of descendant evidence
comment: A type of phylogenetic evidence whereby an aspect of an ancestral gene is inferred through the characterization of an aspect of a descendant gene.

term: acetylation assay evidence
comment: A type of direct assay evidence where acetylated residues are detected in a protein.

term: rapid divergence from ancestral sequence evidence
comment: A type of phylogenetic evidence characterized by long phylogenetic tree branch lengths following a duplication event.

term: phylogenetic determination of loss of key residues evidence
comment: A type of phylogenetic evidence characterized by the absence of key sequence residues.

term: deacetylation assay evidence
comment: A type of direct assay evidence where the removal of acetyl groups are detected in a protein.

term: assertion method
comment: A means by which a statement is made about an entity.

term: cleavage assay evidence
comment: A type of direct assay evidence where the cleavage of a protein into protein fragments by a protease is detected.

term: nucleotide BLAST evidence used in automatic assertion
comment: A type of nucleotide BLAST evidence that is used in an automatic assertion.

term: protein BLAST evidence used in automatic assertion
comment: A type of protein BLAST evidence that is used in an automatic assertion.

term: combinatorial evidence
comment: A type of evidence in which at least two distinct types of evidence have been integrated.

term: combinatorial evidence used in automatic assertion
comment: A type of combinatorial analysis that is used in an automatic assertion.

term: nucleotide BLAST evidence
comment: A type of BLAST evidence in which nucleotide sequences are aligned.

term: protein BLAST evidence
comment: A type of BLAST evidence in which amino acid or translated nucleotide sequences are aligned.

term: BLAST evidence used in automatic assertion
comment: A type of BLAST evidence that is used in an automatic assertion.

term: automatic assertion
comment: An assertion method that does not involve human review.

term: author statement
comment: A type of documented statement evidence that is based on an assertion by the author of a paper, which is read by a curator.

term: nucleic acid localization evidence
comment: A type of localization evidence based on localization of a specific segment of DNA or RNA within tissue by the application of a complementary strand of nucleic acid to which a reporter molecule (i.e. either radio-, fluorescent- or antigen-labeled probe) is attached and quantified using either autoradiography, fluorescence microscopy, or immunohistochemistry.

term: curator inference
comment: A type of inferential evidence that is based on a conclusion drawn by a curator.

term: BLAST evidence
comment: A type of pairwise sequence alignment evidence obtained with basic local alignment search tool (BLAST).

term: sequence alignment evidence
comment: A type of sequence similarity evidence in which an annotation is made based on a manually-reviewed or published sequence alignment

term: sequence orthology evidence
comment: A type of sequence similarity evidence in which orthology is established by multiple criteria, including amino acid and/or nucleotide sequence comparisons and one or more of the following: phylogenetic analysis, coincident expression, conserved map location, functional complementation, immunological cross-reaction, similarity in subcellular localization, subunit structure, substrate specificity, and response to specific inhibitors.

term: localization evidence
comment: A type of direct assay evidence in which the sub-cellular location of a protein or nucleic acid sequence is determined.

term: match to sequence model evidence
comment: A type of sequence similarity evidence in which the function of a gene product is predicted based on a sequence-based statistical model.

term: expression library screen evidence used in manual assertion
comment: A type of expression library screen evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

term: heterologous protein expression evidence used in manual assertion
comment: A type of heterologous protein expression analysis that is used in a manual assertion.

term: syngeneic transplantation experiment evidence
comment: A type of experimental phenotypic evidence resulting from a transplantation in which the transplanted material (stem cells) is from an individual's identical twin.

term: surface plasmon resonance evidence
comment: A type of physical interaction evidence based on real-time, rapid plasmon generation on the interface between a planar surface and vacuum that measures changes in refractive index close to the sensor surface when an analyte and its immobilized ligand bind to observe and characterize molecular interaction.

term: MHC:ligand binding based MHC restriction evidence used in automatic assertion
comment: A type of MHC:ligand binding based MHC restriction evidence that is used in an automatic assertion.

term: MHC complex binding prediction based MHC restriction evidence used in manual assertion
comment: A type of MHC complex binding prediction based MHC restriction evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

term: TACE activity assay evidence
comment: A type of enzymatic activity assay evidence resulting from the analysis of tumor necrosis factor (TNF)-a converting enzyme (TACE), which releases a soluble TNF-a from the membrane-bound precursor protein.

term: MHC complex binding prediction based MHC restriction evidence used in automatic assertion
comment: A type of MHC complex binding prediction based MHC restriction evidence that is used in an automatic assertion.

term: cRNA to DNA expression microarray evidence used in manual assertion
comment: A type of cRNA to DNA expression microarray evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

term: restriction fragment detection evidence

term: inference of MHC restriction based on shared MHC expression used in manual assertion
comment: A type of inference of MHC restriction based on shared MHC expression that is used in a manual assertion.

term: Nimblegen array evidence used in manual assertion

term: resonant mirror biosensor evidence

term: inference of MHC restriction based on shared MHC expression used in automatic assertion
comment: A type of inference of MHC restriction based on shared MHC expression that is used in an automatic assertion.

term: array-based sequence capture evidence used in manual assertion
comment: A type of array-based sequence capture evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

term: expression library screen evidence
comment: A type of protein expression evidence where a protein of interest is isolated on the basis of its hybridization to an antibody raised to a homologous protein.

term: antibody 34-7-23S-specificity based MHC presentation evidence used in manual assertion
comment: A type of antibody 34-7-23S-specificity based MHC presentation evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

term: RNA protection assay evidence
comment: A type of nuclease protection assay evidence where mRNA is hybridized with radiolabeled RNA probes after which RNAse is added to digest the unbound, nonresistant single-stranded overhang regions, later the remaining probe target hybrids are purified and resolved on denaturing polyacrylamide gel, and quantified by autoradiography.

term: reverse transcription polymerase chain reaction evidence
comment: A type of RNA detection assay evidence where an RNA transcript is reverse transcribed into cDNA and amplified to qualitatively detect gene expression.

term: DNA to cDNA expression microarray evidence
comment: A type of expression microarray evidence where expression levels are quantified by hybridization of fluorescently-labeled DNA to cDNA (reverse transcribed from an unknown RNA sample) immobilized on a solid surface.

term: Nimblegen array evidence
comment: A type of cDNA to DNA expression microarray evidence resulting from the use of a proprietary NimbleGen array to measure expression levels.

term: northern blot evidence
comment: A type of transcript expression evidence based on electrophoresis and probing to determine levels of RNA expression using a complementary hybridization probe on the separated RNA samples.

term: fractionation evidence
comment: A type of direct assay evidence resulting from the separation of various cell components while preserving their individual functions.

term: Affymetrix GeneChip evidence
comment: A type of cRNA to DNA expression microarray evidence resulting from the use of a proprietary Affymetrix GeneChip System for analyzing complex genetic information.

term: co-fractionation evidence
comment: A type of fractionation evidence resulting from a protein fractionated with other compounds, factors, or macromolecules.

term: antibody B22-249.R1-specificity based MHC presentation evidence
comment: A type of antibody-specificity based MHC presentation evidence that employs antibody B22-249.R1 to determine that the H2-Db protein complex presented a ligand.

term: protein separation followed by fragment identification evidence
comment: A type of protein separation evidence which then utilizes the screening and identification of small-molecules that bind to proteins.

term: adoptive cell transfer evidence
comment: A type of ex vivo assay evidence derived by ex vivo selection of tumor-reactive lymphocytes, and their activation and numerical expansion before re-infusion to the autologous tumor-bearing host.

term: adhesion assay evidence
comment: A type of cell-based assay evidence resulting from the analysis of cell binding either to extracellular matrix proteins or other cells.

term: allograft transplantation phenotypic evidence
comment: A type of anatomical perturbation phenotypic evidence resulting from the transplantation of an organ or tissue from one individual of the same species with a different genotype.

term: antibody B7/21-specificity based MHC presentation evidence
comment: A type of antibody-specificity based MHC presentation evidence that employs antibody B7/21 to determine that the HLA-DP protein complex presented a ligand.

term: alamarBlue assay evidence
comment: A type of cell viability assay evidence resulting from the continuous measurement of fluorescence intensity from the viable cells, where a cell permeable compound, resazurin (the active ingredient of alamarBlue), is reduced to fluorescent resorufin.

term: antibody B8.11.2-specificity based MHC presentation evidence
comment: A type of antibody-specificity based MHC presentation evidence that employs antibody B8.11.2 to determine that the HLA-DR protein complex presented a ligand.

term: [3H]-thymidine incorporation assay evidence
comment: A type of DNA synthesis cell proliferation assay evidence resulting from the measurement of cell proliferation rate by determining the incorporation of [3H]-thymidine into cellular nucleic acids.

term: antibody B8-24-3-specificity based MHC presentation evidence
comment: A type of antibody-specificity based MHC presentation evidence that employs antibody B8-24-3 to determine that the mouse MHC class I protein complex with H2-b haplotype and/or mouse MHC protein complex with H2-p haplotype presented a ligand.

term: protein separation evidence
comment: A type of fractionation evidence resulting from the isolation of a single type of protein from a complex mixture.

term: [3H]arachidonic acid release assay evidence
comment: A type of cell-based assay evidence resulting from labeling cells with [3H]arachidonic acid and subsequently determining the release of the arachidonic acid by the cells.

term: antibody BB7.2-specificity based MHC presentation evidence
comment: A type of antibody-specificity based MHC presentation evidence that employs antibody BB7.2 to determine that HLA protein complex with A2 serotype presented a ligand.

term: 7-aminoactinomycin staining evidence
comment: A type of apoptotic assay evidence resulting from the use of 7-aminoactinomycin D (7-AAD) to distinguish viable, apoptotic, and dead cells, using the fact that permeability of the cell membrane, and fluorescence intensity, is low in early apoptotic cells and high in late apoptotic and dead cells.

term: antibody C7709A2-specificity based MHC presentation evidence
comment: A type of antibody-specificity based MHC presentation evidence that employs antibody C7709A2 to determine that HLA protein complex with A24 serotype presented a ligand.

term: protein separation followed by direct sequencing evidence
comment: A type of protein separation evidence that is followed by direct protein sequencing whereby a protein's amino acid sequence is determined experimentally by Edman degradation or by mass spectrometry.

term: 51Cr release assay evidence
comment: A type of cytotoxicity assay evidence resulting from the measurement of the amount of radioactive 51Cr released in the supernatant of a sample of 51Cr pre-labeled cells via cytolysis by effector cells (cytotoxic T-cells).

term: antibody CR11-351-specificity based MHC presentation evidence
comment: A type of antibody-specificity based MHC presentation evidence that employs antibody CR11-351 to determine that HLA protein complex with A2 serotype and/or HLA protein complex with A28 serotype presented a ligand.

term: antibody DK1G8-specificity based MHC presentation evidence
comment: A type of antibody-specificity based MHC presentation evidence that employs antibody DK1G8 to determine that HLA protein complex with A29 serotype presented a ligand.

term: in vitro recombinant protein transcription reconstitution assay evidence
comment: A type of in vitro transcription reconstitution assay evidence resulting from the use of recombinant proteins in preparation of a fully-defined transcription system.

term: antibody DT9-specificity based MHC presentation evidence
comment: A type of antibody-specificity based MHC presentation evidence that employs antibody DT9 to determine that the HLA-C protein complex presented a ligand.

term: 3D cell culture evidence
comment: A type of cell proliferation assay evidence resulting from the growth of cells in a micro-environment that mimics real tissue and establishes physiological cell-cell and cell-substrate interactions that regulate proliferation and differentiation.

term: antibody HB145-specificity based MHC presentation evidence
comment: A type of antibody-specificity based MHC presentation evidence that employs antibody HB145 to determine that the human MHC class II protein complex presented a ligand.

term: heterologous protein expression evidence
comment: A type of protein expression evidence where a gene from one cell is inserted into a cell that does not typically contain that gene and heterologous protein expression is assessed.

term: antibody HB-164-specificity based MHC presentation evidence
comment: A type of antibody-specificity based MHC presentation evidence that employs antibody HB-164 to determine that the human MHC class I protein complex presented a ligand.

term: in vitro transcription reconstitution assay evidence
comment: A type of reconstitution assay evidence resulting from the use of reconstituted polymerase transcription systems to investigate RNA synthesis.

term: antibody HB180-specificity based MHC presentation evidence
comment: A type of antibody-specificity based MHC presentation evidence that employs antibody HB180 to determine that the human MHC class II protein complex presented a ligand.

term: antibody ILA-21-specificity based MHC presentation evidence
comment: A type of antibody-specificity based MHC presentation evidence that employs antibody ILA-21 to determine that the cattle MHC class II protein complex presented a ligand.

term: antibody ILA-88-specificity based MHC presentation evidence
comment: A type of antibody-specificity based MHC presentation evidence that employs antibody ILA-88 to determine that the cattle MHC class I protein complex presented a ligand.

term: Southwestern blot evidence
comment: A type of nucleic acid binding evidence in which DNA-protein binding is detected using labeled DNA as probes, hybridized to electrophoretically separated proteins.

term: antibody IVD12-specificity based MHC presentation evidence
comment: A type of antibody-specificity based MHC presentation evidence that employs antibody IVD12 to determine that HLA protein complex with DQ3 serotype presented a ligand.

term: antibody L243-specificity based MHC presentation evidence
comment: A type of antibody-specificity based MHC presentation evidence that employs antibody L243 to determine that the HLA-DR protein complex presented a ligand.

term: Northwestern blot evidence
comment: A type of nucleic acid binding evidence in which RNA-protein binding is detected using labeled RNA as probes, hybridized to electrophoretically separated proteins.

term: antibody LB3.1-specificity based MHC presentation evidence
comment: A type of antibody-specificity based MHC presentation evidence that employs antibody LB3.13 to determine that the HLA-DR protein complex presented a ligand.

term: antibody M1/42-specificity based MHC presentation evidence
comment: A type of antibody-specificity based MHC presentation evidence that employs antibody M1/42 to determine that the mouse MHC class I protein complex presented a ligand.

term: thin layer chromatography evidence
comment: A type of chromatography evidence that uses a thin layer of adsorbent (such as silica gel, alumina, or cellulose) on a flat, inert substrate.

term: antibody M5/114-specificity based MHC presentation evidence
comment: A type of antibody-specificity based MHC presentation evidence that employs antibody M5/114 to determine that the mouse MHC class II protein complex presented a ligand.

term: antibody ME1-specificity based MHC presentation evidence
comment: A type of antibody-specificity based MHC presentation evidence that employs antibody ME1 to determine that the HLA protein complex with B27 serotype presented a ligand.

term: protein:ion binding evidence
comment: A type of protein binding evidence resulting from a metal ion binding to a protein at a specific binding site.

term: antibody MKD6-specificity based MHC presentation evidence
comment: A type of antibody-specificity based MHC presentation evidence that employs antibody MKD6 to determine that the H2-IAd protein complex presented a ligand.

term: antibody OX18-specificity based MHC presentation evidence
comment: A type of antibody-specificity based MHC presentation evidence that employs antibody OX18 to determine that the rat MHC class I protein complex presented a ligand.

term: ribohomopolymer binding assay evidence
comment: A type of nucleic acid binding evidence resulting from an enzyme displaying binding activity to specific ribohomopolymer.

term: antibody PT85-A-specificity based MHC presentation evidence
comment: A type of antibody-specificity based MHC presentation evidence that employs antibody PT85-A to determine that the pig MHC class I protein complex, cattle MHC class I protein complex, and/or human MHC class I protein complex presented a ligand.

term: antibody SF1-1.1.1-specificity based MHC presentation evidence
comment: A type of antibody-specificity based MHC presentation evidence that employs antibody SF1-1.1.1 to determine that the H2-Kd protein complex presented a ligand.

term: antibody SPVL3-specificity based MHC presentation evidence
comment: A type of antibody-specificity based MHC presentation evidence that employs antibody SPVL3 to determine that the human MHC class II protein complex presented a ligand.

term: antibody Tu39-specificity based MHC presentation evidence
comment: A type of antibody-specificity based MHC presentation evidence that employs antibody Tu39 to determine that the human MHC class II protein complex presented a ligand.

term: transport assay evidence
comment: A type of direct assay evidence resulting from the activity assessment of transport proteins.

term: antibody W6/32-specificity based MHC presentation evidence
comment: A type of antibody-specificity based MHC presentation evidence that employs antibody W6/32 to determine that the MHC class I protein complex presented a ligand.

term: antibody Y-3-specificity based MHC presentation evidence
comment: A type of antibody-specificity based MHC presentation evidence that employs antibody Y-3 to determine that theH2-Kb protein complex, H2-Ks protein complex, and/or H2-Kq protein complex presented a ligand.

term: nucleic acid binding evidence
comment: A type of affinity evidence resulting from the binding of a molecule to a nucleic acid.

term: antibody Y3JP-specificity based MHC presentation evidence
comment: A type of antibody-specificity based MHC presentation evidence that employs antibody Y3JP to determine that the mouse MHC class II protein complex and/or rat MHC class II protein complex with RT1-A haplotype presented a ligand.

term: protein expression-based MHC presentation evidence
comment: A type of protein expression evidence that employs MHC molecule motif or alleles present to determine that a specific MHC molecule or class of MHC molecules presented a ligand.

term: beta-glucuronidase fusion protein localization evidence
comment: A type of fusion protein localization evidence resulting from the targeted insertion of the beta-glucuronidase (GUS) coding gene as a reporter gene for the localization of a particular gene product.

term: specific MHC protein expression-based MHC presentation evidence
comment: A type of protein expression-based MHC presentation evidence that employs knowledge of a single specific MHC molecule's presence to determine that a specific MHC molecule presented a ligand.

term: beta-galactosidase fusion protein localization evidence
comment: A type of fusion protein localization evidence resulting from the targeted insertion of the beta-galactosidase coding gene (lacZ) into a specific gene to create a beta-galactosidase-tagged fusion protein.

term: MHC:ligand binding based MHC restriction evidence
comment: A type of protein binding evidence that employs an assay measuring binding of an MHC molecule to a ligand to determine that T cells can recognize the ligand when presented by that MHC molecule.

term: green fluorescent protein fusion protein localization evidence
comment: A type of fusion protein localization evidence resulting from the labeling of a protein of interest with green fluorescent protein (GFP) from the jellyfish Aequorea victoria.

term: MHC complex binding prediction based MHC restriction evidence
comment: A type of computational evidence that employs a computational tool to predict MHC complex binding to a ligand to infer that T cells can recognize the ligand when presented by that MHC molecule.

term: inference of MHC restriction based on shared MHC expression
comment: A type of inferential evidence that employs the association of specific MHC molecule expression by a subject population with a T cell response to infer that T cells can recognize the ligand when presented by that MHC molecule.

term: yellow fluorescent protein fusion protein localization evidence
comment: A type of fusion protein localization evidence resulting from the labeling of a protein of interest with yellow fluorescent protein (YFP), which was created by mutating green fluorescent protein (GFP) of the Aequorea victoria.

term: T cell epitope assay type based MHC restriction evidence
comment: A type of direct assay evidence that employs the type of T cell epitope assay to determine that a specific ligand is restricted by a MHC molecule or class of MHC molecules.

term: MHC-specific blocking based MHC restriction evidence
comment: A type of protein binding evidence that employs the specific blocking of MHC molecules to determine that a ligand is restricted by that MHC molecule or class of MHC molecules.

term: protein localization evidence
comment: A type of localization evidence where sub-cellular localization of a protein is determined.

term: specific MHC molecule based MHC restriction evidence
comment: A type of direct assay evidence that employs the use of a specific MHC molecule in a T cell response assay to determine that a specific ligand is restricted by that MHC molecule.

term: T cell type based MHC restriction evidence
comment: A type of direct assay evidence that employs a specific T cell type (CD4+ or CD8+) to determine that a ligand is restricted by a class of MHC molecules.

term: fusion protein localization evidence
comment: A type of protein localization evidence resulting from the fusion of a protein of interest to a labeling protein which has enzymatic activity or fluorescence properties.

term: antibody-specificity based MHC presentation evidence used in manual assertion
comment: A type of antibody-specificity based MHC presentation evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

term: antibody-specificity based MHC presentation evidence used in automatic assertion
comment: A type of antibody-specificity based MHC presentation evidence that is used in an automatic assertion.

term: antibody 10.3.6-specificity based MHC presentation evidence used in manual assertion
comment: A type of antibody 10.3.6-specificity based MHC presentation evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

term: over expression analysis evidence
comment: A type of experimental phenotypic evidence in which a gene and/or gene product is investigated in a transgenic organism that has been engineered to overexpress that gene product.

term: histochemistry evidence
comment: A type of histology evidence resulting from the identification of chemical components in cells and tissues.

term: high-performance liquid chromatography evidence
comment: A type of chromatography evidence resulting from the separation of molecules in a solute by forcing the solvent containing the sample through a column packed with nonporous particles at high pressure.

term: histology evidence
comment: A type of imaging assay evidence resulting from the qualitative microscopic examination of cells or tissues.

term: fluorescence in situ hybridization evidence
comment: A type of nucleic acid localization evidence and in situ hybridization evidence resulting from the use of fluorescent probes to detect complementary sequences of nucleic acids.

term: filter binding assay evidence
comment: A type of physical interaction evidence resulting from a mixture of two molecules passed through a nitrocellulose filter, where one may be immobilized on the filter, and if the immobilized molecule is capable of binding to the other, it will be retained on the filter as well.

term: gel-filtration evidence
comment: A type of chromatography evidence resulting from the exclusion of proteins based on molecular size by filtration through a porous matrix (swollen gel), from which larger molecules are excluded.

term: fluorescence resonance energy transfer evidence
comment: A type of dynamic fluorescence quenching evidence resulting from the measurement of the proximity of two fluorophores, where the energy from an excited molecular fluorophore to another fluorophore can only occur within ~10nm.

term: Edman degradation evidence used in manual assertion
comment: A type of Edman degradation evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

term: dominant-negative mutant phenotypic evidence
comment: A type of mutant phenotype evidence resulting from a mutated gene producing mutant polypeptides that disrupt the activity of the wild-type genes.

term: eTag assay evidence
comment: A type of affinity evidence resulting from the quantitative analysis of gene and protein expression monitored by proprietary eTag reporters.

term: Edman degradation evidence
comment: A type of protein detection assay evidence resulting from labeling a termonal amino acid residue and cleaving it from a peptide by sequentially removing one residue at a time from the amino end of the peptide, without disrupting the bonds.

term: RNA dot blot assay evidence
comment: A type of RNA detection assay evidence based on the direct application of a RNA mixture in a circular motion on a matrix for hybridization with labeled DNA fragments.

term: DNA laddering assay evidence
comment: A type of apoptotic assay evidence resulting from the visualization via gel electrophoresis of the fragmented DNA (DNA ladder) which is the result of apoptotic DNA fragmentation.

term: cytochrome C release assay evidence
comment: A type of apoptotic assay evidence resulting from the identification of an accumulation of cytochrome C in the cytoplasm after its release from the mitochondria, an early event in apoptosis.

term: cytochemistry evidence
comment: A type of histochemistry evidence resulting from localizing chemical components of cells and organelles on histological sections.

term: deletion mutation phenotypic evidence
comment: A type of mutant phenotype evidence resulting from a mutation in which there is the removal of one or more contiguous nucleotides that may result in altered function or other measurable properties.

term: 4',6-diamidino-2-phenylindole staining evidence
comment: A type of staining evidence resulting from 4',6-diamidino-2-phenylindole (DAPI) binding to AT regions of DNA and emitting a blue fluorescence.

term: enzyme inhibition evidence
comment: A type of protein inhibition evidence and enzymatic acitivty evidence where the protein under study is an enzyme.

term: constitutively active mutant protein evidence
comment: A type of mutant phenotypic evidence resulting from a mutation causing a change to a protein sequence that produces a constitutively active mutant protein (CAM), that remains active in the absence of upstream signals.

term: conditional knockin evidence
comment: A type of knockin evidence resulting from the targeted introduction of a temporally-restricted and/or tissue-specific mutation.

term: crystallography evidence
comment: A type of structure determination evidence resulting from the use of a narrow beam of x-rays to identify molecular structures by creating a diffraction pattern.

term: cross-linking evidence
comment: A type of protein binding evidence resulting from the identification of two interacting proteins (that exist in close proximity) by linking through covalent bonds followed by identification

term: clinical study evidence
comment: A type of experimental evidence arising from a controlled investigation that uses human subjects.

term: in vitro assay evidence
comment: A type of direct assay evidence resulting from a process performed outside the living organism, where the components of an organism have been isolated from their usual biological context, to permit a more detailed or more convenient analysis in an artificial setting.

term: conditional knockout evidence
comment: A type of knockout evidence resulting from a temporally-restricted and/or tissue-specific targeted gene removal.

term: cell-free assay evidence
comment: A type of direct assay evidence resulting from studies in which cytoplasmic and/or nuclear cellular components from resting, nonstimulated cells, are isolated by ultracentrifugation to provide molecular machinery that can be used in reactions in the absence of many of the other cellular components for the purpose of in vitro protein synthesis, transcription, DNA replication, etc.

term: comet assay evidence
comment: A type of gel electrophoresis evidence resulting in the assessment of DNA breakage in a cell, based on size and shape of DNA migration.

term: co-sedimentation assay evidence
comment: A type of physical interaction evidence resulting from the separation of a mixture of molecules under the influence of a force such as artificial gravity, where molecules sedimenting together are assumed to interact.

term: genomic context evidence
comment: A type of similarity evidence in which the location of the gene within the genome provides insight into the gene's function or evolutionary insight.

term: co-electrophoresis evidence
comment: A type of gel electrophoresis evidence resulting from the electrophoresis of two substances together, allowing for the characterization of ligand/nucleic acid binding interactions.

term: in vivo assay evidence
comment: A type of direct assay evidence resulting from a sample of microorganisms or living tissue grown in a medium.

term: chimeric protein phenotypic evidence
comment: A type of mutant phenotype evidence resulting from the fusion of two or more different genes to create one protein product.

term: animal model system study evidence
comment: A type of experimental evidence arising from the investigation of an animal model system.

term: colony counting evidence
comment: A type of direct assay evidence resulting from the counting of microbial colonies that arise from viable cells grown on a plate or dish.

term: co-localization evidence
comment: A type of imaging assay evidence resulting from the limited observation of the co-occurrence of molecules in a subcellular location.

term: cell permeability assay evidence
comment: A type of cell-based assay evidence resulting from the quantification of cell permeability.

term: mutant physiological response evidence
comment: A type of mutant phenotype evidence in which the physiological response of a mutant when presented with an external stimulus is determined.

term: cell counting evidence
comment: A type of cell-based assay evidence resulting from the quantification of a sample of cells.

term: chemiluminescence-linked immunoassay evidence
comment: A type of protein detection assay evidence resulting from a complex (a chemiluminescent compound, protein and a steroidal hapten) utilized as a labeled antigen, which emits light when treated with hydrogen peroxide and copper acetate at a high pH.

term: mutant visible phenotype evidence
comment: A type of mutant phenotype evidence in which traits arising from a mutation are visually examined.

term: carboxyfluorescein diacetate succinimidyl ester staining evidence
comment: A type of staining evidence resulting from monitoring division by the use of carboxyfluorescein diacetate succinimidyl ester (CFSE) to label intracellular molecules with carboxyfluorescein. when a labeled cell divides, the number of carboxyfluorescein-tagged molecules is split.

term: transcriptional activation assay evidence
comment: A type of transcription assay evidence in which sequence-specific binding proteins that increase transcription of a specific target gene or genes are identified, quantified, and/or analyzed.

term: biochemical trait analysis evidence
comment: A type of experimental phenotypic evidence in which the biochemical aspect of a mutation is analyzed.

term: bromodeoxyuridine incorporation assay evidence
comment: A type of nucleotide analog incorporation evidence resulting from the incorporation of bromodeoxyuridine (BrdU) as a thymidine analog into nuclear DNA, resulting in a label that can be tracked using antibody probes.

term: Boyden chamber assay evidence
comment: A type of chemotaxis assay evidence where the presence or absence of positive or negative chemotaxis is determined by measuring the number of cells that migrate from the upper compartment of a chamber (separated by a micro-porous membrane) to the lower compartment, in which chemotactic agents are present.

term: caspase assay evidence
comment: A type of apoptotic assay evidence resulting from the detection of caspase activation, which results in the cleaving of intracellular substrates during apoptosis.

term: two-electrode voltage clamp recording evidence
comment: A type of voltage clamp recording evidence which involves using two electrodes inserted into a large cell (often a xenopus oocyte) where one electrode is used to measure the internal potential (voltage) of the cell and the other electrode is used to clamp the current.

term: blocking peptide evidence
comment: A type of immunological assay evidence resulting from the use of peptides to block antibodies from binding to their targets.

term: blocking monoclonal antibody evidence
comment: A type of immunological assay evidence resulting from inhibitory effect of monoclonal antibody combining with an antigen over other antibodies.

term: transcription assay evidence
comment: A type of direct assay evidence resulting from the detection and quantification of transcribed RNA.

term: blood test evidence
comment: A type of direct assay evidence where a blood sample is extracted from an organism to analyze different blood components.

term: blocking polyclonal antibody evidence
comment: A type of immunological assay evidence resulting from the inhibitory effect of polyclonal antibodies (antibodies secreted by different B cell lineages), which while not reacting with a specific antigen, serve to prevent other antibodies from doing so.

term: heterologous system uptake evidence
comment: A type of transport assay evidence in which the uptake mechanism of a transporter is investigated in a cell that does not normally express that protein.

term: anion-exchange chromatography evidence
comment: A type of chromatography evidence where a positively charged ion exchange resin with an affinity for molecules having net negative surface charges is used to separate the molecules.

term: electrophysiology assay evidence
comment: A type of direct assay evidence where electrical properties of cells or tissues are studied.

term: cognitive assay phenotypic evidence
comment: A type of experimental phenotypic evidence resulting from behavioral phenotyping and analysis to assess cognitive functioning.

term: annexin-V staining evidence
comment: A type of apoptotic assay evidence resulting from the addition and subsequent binding of Annexin V to phosphatidylserine in cells to detect if they are viable, apoptotic, or necrotic.

term: macroscopy evidence
comment: A type of experimental evidence that is visible to the naked eye cf. microscopy evidence which requires the aid of a microscope.

term: ribosome profiling evidence used in automatic assertion
comment: A type of ribosome profiling evidence that is used in an automatic assertion.

term: luminescence-based mammalian interactome mapping assay evidence
comment: A type of physical interaction evidence resulting from the analysis of protein-protein interactions by use of a luciferase enzyme fused to a particular protein (or proteins), which are coexpressed with epitope-tagged partners in mammalian cells.

term: mass spectrometry evidence
comment: A type of spectrometry evidence resulting from identifying the amount and type of material entities present in a sample by fragmenting it and measuring the mass-to-charge ratio of the resulting particles.

term: mammalian 2-hybrid assay evidence
comment: A type of bait-prey hybrid interaction evidence resulting from the analysis of proteins of interest attached to two portions of the transcriptional activator, and in interaction bring the two portions together to increase expression of the reporter gene.

term: knockin evidence
comment: A type of genetic transformation evidence resulting from the targetted replacement of a wild-type DNA sequence with a different sequence.

term: lipid binding assay evidence
comment: A type of physical interaction evidence resulting from the qualitative and quantitative analysis of the affinity with which a protein binds to a lipid.

term: knockout phenotypic evidence
comment: A type of genetic transformation evidence resulting from a change in the DNA that results in the elimination of the function of the gene, allowing for functional analysis.

term: Etest evidence used in automatic assertion
comment: A type of Etest evidence that is used in an automatic assertion.

term: zone of inhibition evidence used in automatic assertion
comment: A type of zone of inhibition evidence that is used in an automatic assertion.

term: colony size phenotypic evidence used in automatic assertion
comment: A type of colony size phenotypic evidence that is used in an automatic assertion.

term: colony color phenotypic evidence used in automatic assertion
comment: A type of colony color phenotypic evidence that is used in an automatic assertion.

term: colony morphology phenotypic evidence used in automatic assertion
comment: A type of colony morphology phenotypic evidence that is used in an automatic assertion.

term: phenomic profiling assay evidence used in automatic assertion
comment: A type of phenomic profiling assay evidence that is used in an automatic assertion.

term: in vivo transcription assay evidence
comment: A type of transcription assay evidence used in an in vivo experiment.

term: bacterial 2-hybrid assay evidence used in automatic assertion
comment: A type of bacterial 2-hybrid assay evidence that is used in an automatic assertion.

term: in vivo sumoylation assay evidence
comment: A type of sumoylation assay evidence used in an in vivo experiment.

term: flow cell biofilm assay evidence used in automatic assertion
comment: A type of flow cell biofilm assay evidence that is used in an automatic assertion.

term: in vivo ubiquitination assay evidence
comment: A type of ubiquitination assay evidence used in an in vivo experiment.

term: crystal violet staining evidence used in automatic assertion
comment: A type of crystal violet staining evidence that is used in an automatic assertion.

term: in vivo translation assay evidence
comment: A type of translation assay evidence used in an in vivo experiment.

term: colony papillation assay phenotypic evidence used in automatic assertion
comment: A type of colony papillation assay phenotypic evidence that is used in an automatic assertion.

term: in vivo palmitoylation assay evidence
comment: A type of palmitoylation assay evidence used in an in vivo experiment.

term: in vivo methylation assay evidence
comment: A type of methylation assay evidence used in an in vivo experiment.

term: in vivo protein kinase assay evidence
comment: A type of protein kinase assay evidence used in an in vivo experiment.

term: in vivo phosphatase assay evidence
comment: A type of phosphatase assay evidence used in an in vivo experiment.

term: in vivo farnesylation assay evidence
comment: A type of farnesylation assay evidence used in an in vivo experiment.

term: in vivo desumoylation assay evidence
comment: A type of desumoylation assay evidence used in an in vivo experiment.

term: static light scattering assay evidence used in automatic assertion
comment: A type of static light scattering assay evidence that is used in an automatic assertion.

term: dynamic light scattering assay evidence used in automatic assertion
comment: A type of dynamic light scattering assay evidence that is used in an automatic assertion.

term: light scattering evidence used in automatic assertion
comment: A type of light scattering evidence that is used in an automatic assertion.

term: confocal laser scanning microscopy evidence used in automatic assertion
comment: A type of confocal laser scanning microscopy evidence that is used in an automatic assertion.

term: in vivo deubiquitination assay evidence
comment: A type of deubiquitination assay evidence used in an in vivo experiment.

term: extended field laser confocal microscopy evidence used in automatic assertion
comment: A type of extended field laser confocal microscopy evidence that is used in an automatic assertion.

term: differential interference contrast microscopy evidence used in automatic assertion
comment: A type of differential interference contrast microscopy evidence that is used in an automatic assertion.

term: koehler illumination microscopy evidence used in automatic assertion
comment: A type of koehler illumination microscopy evidence that is used in an automatic assertion.

term: in vivo deacetylation assay evidence
comment: A type of deacetylation assay evidence used in an in vivo experiment.

term: transmitted light brightfied mircoscopy evidence used in automatic assertion
comment: A type of transmitted light brightfied mircoscopy evidence that is used in an automatic assertion.

term: in vivo cleavage assay evidence
comment: A type of cleavage assay evidence used in an in vivo experiment.

term: phase contrast microscopy evidence used in automatic assertion
comment: A type of phase contrast microscopy evidence that is used in an automatic assertion.

term: in vivo demethylation assay evidence
comment: A type of demethylation assay evidence used in an in vivo experiment.

term: time-lapsed microscopy evidence used in automatic assertion
comment: A type of time-lapsed microscopy evidence that is used in an automatic assertion.

term: in vivo defarnesylation assay evidence
comment: A type of defarnesylation assay evidence used in an in vivo experiment.

term: in vitro translation assay evidence
comment: A type of translation assay evidence used in an in vitro experiment.

term: in vitro transcription assay evidence
comment: A type of transcription assay evidence used in an in vitro experiment.

term: in vivo acetylation assay evidence
comment: A type of acetylation assay evidence used in an in vivo experiment.

term: in vitro ubiquitination assay evidence
comment: A type of ubiquitination assay evidenceused in an in vitro experiment.

term: in vitro sumoylation assay evidence
comment: A type of sumoylation assay evidence used in an in vitro experiment.

term: scanning electron microscopy evidence used in automatic assertion
comment: A type of scanning electron microscopy evidence that is used in an automatic assertion.

term: transmission electron microscopy evidence used in automatic assertion
comment: A type of transmission electron microscopy evidence that is used in an automatic assertion.

term: epifluorescence microscopy evidence used in automatic assertion
comment: A type of epifluorescence microscopy evidence that is used in an automatic assertion.

term: plaque assay evidence used in automatic assertion
comment: A type of plaque assay evidence that is used in an automatic assertion.

term: in vitro polyADP-ribosylation assay evidence
comment: A type of polyADP-ribosylation assay evidence used in an in vitro experiment.

term: 5-cyano-2,3-ditolyl tetrazolium chloride staining evidence used in automatic assertion
comment: A type of 5-cyano-2,3-ditolyl tetrazolium chloride staining evidence that is used in an automatic assertion.

term: in vitro protein kinase assay evidence
comment: A type of protein kinase assay evidence used in an in vitro experiment.

comment: A type of functional complementation evidence resulting from the introduction of nucleic acids, which are not permanently incorporated into the genome, to temporarily prevent, or "rescue" an organism from a condition.

term: author statement without traceable support
comment: A type of author statement that is not associated with results presented or a cited reference.

term: no evidence data found
comment: A type of curator inference that results when research finds no evidence information in the scientific literature, at reference databases, or from other resources.

term: BLAST evidence used in manual assertion
comment: A type of BLAST evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

term: protein BLAST evidence used in manual assertion
comment: A type of protein BLAST evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

term: nucleotide BLAST evidence used in manual assertion
comment: A type of nucleotide BLAST evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

term: author statement supported by traceable reference
comment: A type of author statement in which the author makes a statement that is not supported by information in that particular publication, but rather can be traced to a reference cited by that publication.

term: structural similarity evidence
comment: A type of similarity evidence based on structural similarity of an annotated gene or gene product to another gene or group of genes.

term: motif similarity evidence
comment: A type of match to sequence model evidence that is based on the presence of a recognized domain or motif in a gene product's (usually protein) primary sequence.

term: match to InterPro member signature evidence
comment: A type of match to sequence model evidence resulting from a positive match of a protein, or set of proteins to a predictive model (signature) in the InterPro database.

term: affinity evidence
comment: A type of physical interaction evidence that depends on the strength of the interaction between two entities.

term: protein binding evidence
comment: A type of affinity evidence resulting from the binding of a molecule to a protein or protein complex.

term: bait-prey hybrid interaction evidence
comment: A type of protein binding evidence where proteins of interest (bait and prey) are covalently linked to incomplete fragments of a third protein (reporter) and expressed in vivo, at which time interaction between bait and prey proteins brings reporter fragments in close enough proximity to allow them to reform and become a functional reporter protein.

term: protein inhibition evidence
comment: A type of direct assay evidence based on the inhibition of the molecular function of a protein.

term: physical interaction evidence
comment: A type of experimental evidence that is based on characterization of an interaction between a gene product and another molecule.

term: co-purification evidence
comment: A type of physical interaction evidence where a cellular component subunit is isolated as part of purification of its larger complex.

term: loss-of-function mutant phenotype evidence
comment: A type of mutant phenotype evidence where a phenotype is associated with altered gene product which lacks the molecular function of the wild-type gene.

term: ectopic expression evidence
comment: A type of experimental phenotypic evidence where a transgenic strain carrying the construct of a promoter cDNA fusion in which a gene of interest is driven by a defined promoter or enhancer is ectopically expressed in the defined pattern to characterize potential cellular properties and functions of a protein of interest.

term: anti-sense experiment evidence
comment: A type of mutant phenotype evidence where a phenotype is observed while expressing an anti-sense version of a gene product in a wild-type (for that gene product) background.

term: RNAi evidence
comment: A type of mutant phenotype evidence where an RNA construct is introduced into a cell and the expression of the gene bearing its complementary sequence is suppressed.

term: functional complementation evidence
comment: A type of genetic interaction evidence where a wild-type copy of the gene in question is inserted into a mutant cell to see if it restores the wild-type phenotype in the mutant background.

term: transgenic rescue experiment evidence
comment: A type of functional complementation evidence resulting from the introduction of a transgene to prevent, or "rescue" an organism from a condition.

term: mutant phenotype evidence
comment: A type of experimental phenotypic evidence in which an observable phenotypic difference results from a change or mutation in DNA.

term: protein expression evidence
comment: A type of expression pattern evidence resulting from protein abundance quantification techniques.

term: genetic interaction evidence
comment: A type of experimental phenotypic evidence resulting from the effect that a given gene has on another gene or genes, and the products.

term: transcript expression evidence
comment: A type of expression pattern evidence where abundance of a transcript is analyzed.

term: enzymatic activity assay evidence
comment: A type of protein assay evidence where the catalytic activity of an enzyme is determined.

term: experimental evidence
comment: A type of evidence that is the output of a scientific procedure performed to make a discovery, test a hypothesis, or demonstrate a known fact.

term: immunofluorescence evidence
comment: A type of protein detection assay evidence where a fluorescently labeled antibody is used to detect the presence or localization of a biomolecule within a cell.

term: expression pattern evidence
comment: A type of experimental evidence that is based on characterization of gene expression.

term: inference from background scientific knowledge
comment: A type of curator inference where conclusions are drawn based on the background scientific knowledge of the curator.

term: direct assay evidence
comment: A type of experimental evidence resulting from the direct measurement of some aspect of a biological feature.

term: reconstitution assay evidence
comment: A type of direct assay evidence based on reconstructing a biological sample from its disassociated state to its original state.

term: cell fractionation evidence
comment: A type of fractionation evidence where sub-cellular components are separated based on their physical properties such as density in a sucrose density gradient.

term: evidence
comment: A type of information that is used to support an assertion.

term: targeting sequence prediction evidence
comment: A type of motif similarity evidence that is based on detection of a targeting sequence in the primary sequence of a protein through computational prediction and/or a manual examination of the sequence.

term: transmembrane domain prediction evidence
comment: A type of motif similarity evidence that is based on detection of one, or more, transmembrane domains in the primary sequence of a protein through computational prediction and/or a manual examination of the sequence.

term: gene neighbors evidence
comment: A type of genomic context evidence in which a gene product's identity is supported on the basis of the identity of neighboring genes.

term: phylogenetic evidence
comment: A type of similarity that indicates common ancestry.

term: southern hybridization evidence
comment: A type of DNA detection assay evidence that is based on detection of a specific DNA sequence by hybridization of labeled probes to any immobilized DNA fragment with sequence similarity.

term: affinity chromatography evidence
comment: A type of affinity evidence that results from separation of biochemical mixtures by selective binding of a compound to an immobilized compound on a polymeric matrix, subsequent removal of unattached components, and then displacement of the bound compound.

term: split-ubiquitin functional complementation evidence
comment: A type of protein fragment functional complementation evidence that is based on detection of protein-protein interaction between a bait and prey protein by in vivo reconstitution of split-ubiquitin (when bait and prey interact) and release of a reporter protein.

term: gene expression similarity evidence
comment: A type of phenotypic similarity evidence that is based on the categorization of genes by the similarity of expression profiles.

term: far-Western blotting evidence
comment: A type of physical interaction evidence that is based on detection of protein-protein interactions by separation of target proteins by SDS-PAGE which are blotted to a membrane, followed by denaturation and renaturation, probing with purified bait proteins, and detection of the target-bait complexes.

term: methylation-specific polymerase chain reaction evidence
comment: A type of in vitro methylation assay evidence resulting from initial modification of DNA by sodium bisulfite, converting all unmethylated cytosines to uracil, and subsequent amplification with primers specific for methylated versus unmethylated DNA.

term: co-immunoprecipitation evidence
comment: A type of immunoprecipitation evidence that involves precipitating two or more proteins via binding to an antibody specific to a single protein, followed by protein identification.

term: morphological similarity evidence
comment: A type of phenotypic similarity evidence based on the similarity of shape, structure, or configuration in structures.

term: developmental similarity evidence
comment: A type of phenotypic similarity evidence based on the similarity of embryological or post-embryonic orgin of structures.

term: yeast 2-hybrid evidence
comment: A type of bait-prey hybrid interaction evidence that is based on detection of protein-protein interaction by activation of a yeast reporter gene after a bait protein fused to a DNA-binding domain (which has been transfected into a yeast cell) is used to screen a cDNA library of clones fused to an activation domain.

term: differential methylation hybridization evidence
comment: A type of in vitro methylation assay evidence where methylation-sensitive restriction enzymes are utilized to compare differential methylation between two samples by first shearing DNA, followed by end-blunting, ligation of linkers, methylation sensitive restriction, PCR using linker primers, dye labeling and relative quantification of methylated DNA fragments by two-colored array hybridization to a CpG island microarray for visual assessment.

term: compositional similarity evidence
comment: A type of phenotypic similarity evidence based on the similarity of the histological makeup of structures.

term: functional complementation in heterologous system evidence
comment: A type of functional complementation evidence that is based on the insertion of a wild-type copy of a gene into a heterologous organism, with the mutation occurring in a homologous gene.

term: yeast one-hybrid evidence
comment: A type of bait-prey hybrid interaction evidence that is based on a protein-DNA complementation assay where a single promoter acts as bait and is screened against a library of prey transcription factors.

term: positional similarity evidence
comment: A type of phenotypic similarity evidence based on the similarity of stucture locations or arrangements.

term: quantitative trait analysis evidence
comment: A type of phenotypic evidence that is based on a gene product that is associated with a quantitative trait locus, but has not been cloned.

term: cRNA to DNA expression microarray evidence
comment: A type of expression microarray evidence where expression level is quantified by sample biotin-labeled cRNA (transcribed from an unknown RNA sample) hybridized to DNA oligonuclotides immoblized on a solid surface.

term: epistatic interaction phenotypic evidence
comment: A type of genetic interaction evidence resulting from the suppression of one allelic effect by an allele at another genetic locus.

term: phenotypic similarity evidence
comment: A type of similarity based on the expression of a genotype in an environment.

term: expression microarray evidence
comment: A type of transcript expression evidence resulting from simultaneous profiling of the expression levels of thousands of genes in a single experiment allowing analysis of genes and their networks.

term: experimental phenotypic evidence
comment: A type of experimental evidence that is based on an observable characteristic trait, which is the result of the expression of an organisms genotype in an environment.

term: suppressor/enhancer interaction phenotypic evidence
comment: A type of genetic interaction evidence resulting from a second mutation that either suppresses or enhances the phenotype expressed from an original mutation.

term: automatically integrated combinatorial evidence used in automatic assertion
comment: A type of automatically integrated combinatorial evidence that is used in an automatic assertion.

term: double mutant phenotypic evidence
comment: A type of mutant phenotype evidence resulting from an experiment typically constructed to determine if two different genes have an observable genetic interaction (functional connection) as the result of a mutation occurring in the alleles of the two genes of interest.

term: voucher specimen phenotypic analysis evidence
comment: A type of experimental phenotypic evidence based on an authors phenotypic description of a species (or higher-level group), which explicitly references an observation made of a voucher specimen (a specimen with a permanent museum catalog).

term: genetic similarity evidence
comment: A type of similarity based on genotype without respect to expression.

term: reporter gene assay evidence
comment: A type of expression pattern evidence that is based on the expression pattern of a reporter gene.

term: spatial pattern of protein expression evidence
comment: A type of protein expression evidence that accounts for the position of RNA translation to a protein product ranging in scale from differing tissues to regions of an anatomical structure.

term: spatial pattern of transcript expression evidence
comment: A type of transcript expression evidence that accounts for the position of transcription ranging in scale from the position of genes on the chromosome to differing tissues to regions of an anatomical structure.

term: similarity evidence
comment: A type of evidence resulting from comparing likeness of distinct biological entities.

term: gain-of-function mutant phenotypic evidence
comment: A type of mutant phenotype evidence resulting from an altered gene product which possesses a new molecular function or a new pattern of gene expression.

term: sequence similarity evidence
comment: A type of similarity based on biomolecular sequence.

term: ferric uptake regulator titration assay evidence used in automatic assertion
comment: A type of ferric uptake regulator titration assay evidence that is used in an automatic assertion.

term: fluorescence anisotropy evidence used in automatic assertion
comment: A type of fluorescence anisotropy evidence that is used in an automatic assertion.

term: DNAse footprinting evidence used in automatic assertion
comment: A type of DNAse footprinting evidence that is used in an automatic assertion.

term: DNA affinity chromatography evidence used in automatic assertion
comment: A type of DNA affinity chromatography evidence that is used in an automatic assertion.

term: nucleic acid binding evidence used in automatic assertion
comment: A type of nucleic acid binding evidence that is used in an automatic assertion.

term: copper-phenanthroline footprinting evidence used in automatic assertion
comment: A type of copper-phenanthroline footprinting evidence that is used in an automatic assertion.

term: immunoprecipitation evidence used in automatic assertion
comment: A type of immunoprecipitation evidence that is used in an automatic assertion.

term: chromatin immunoprecipitation-PCR evidence used in automatic assertion
comment: A type of chromatin immunoprecipitation-PCR evidence that is used in an automatic assertion.

term: chloramphenicol acetyltransferase reporter gene assay evidence used in automatic assertion
comment: A type of chloramphenicol acetyltransferase reporter gene assay evidence that is used in an automatic assertion.

term: beta-galactosidase reporter gene assay evidence used in automatic assertion
comment: A type of beta-galactosidase reporter gene assay evidence that is used in an automatic assertion.

term: electrophoretic mobility shift assay evidence
comment: A type of affinity evidence based on an electrophoretic mobility shift of macromolecules, where proteins, nucleic acids, or both, are combined and the resulting mixtures are electrophoresed under native conditions through polyacrylamide or agarose gel to detect interactions/complexes between proteins and/or nucleic acid.

term: cDNA to DNA expression microarray evidence
comment: A type of expression microarray evidence where expression level is quantified by fluroescently-labeled cDNA (reverse transcribed from an unknown RNA sample) hybridized to DNA immobilized on a solid surface.

term: epitope-tagged protein immunolocalization evidence
comment: A type of immunolocalization evidence in which recombinant proteins fused with epitopes are recognized by antibodies.

term: array-based sequence capture evidence
comment: A type of DNA detection assay evidence evidence where gene sequence or variation is determined or detected by fluorescently-labeled DNA fragments hybridized to sequence-specific oligonucleotides immobilized on an array.

term: cell growth regulation assay evidence
comment: A type of cell growth assay evidence that measures one or more aspects of cell growth over a specified time period to indicate an induced or repressed regulatory effect.

term: immunogold labelling evidence
comment: A type of immunolocalization evidence where the antibodies are labeled with colloidal gold particles whose location is then detected via microscopy.

term: restriction landmark genomic scanning evidence
comment: A type of DNA detection assay evidence resulting from the use of restriction enzymes for direct end-labeling of DNA (creating landmarks), followed by high-resolution two-dimensional electrophoresis to visualize the landmarks.

term: immunoprecipitation evidence
comment: A type of protein binding evidence where an antibody specific for a target protein is used to precipitate the target protein along with any other molecules (e.g. protein, nucleic acid) that are bound to the target protein.

term: amplification of intermethylated sites evidence
comment: A type of in vitro methylation assay evidence resulting from a genome-wide estimate of DNA methylation by differential enzymatic digestion of genomic DNA with methylation-sensitive and methylation-insensitive isoschizomers, followed by restrained PCR amplification of sequences methylated at both ends and resolving the PCR products in a denaturing polyacrylamide-sequencing gel to generate fingerprints that consist of multiple anonymous bands that represent the DNA methylome of the cell.

term: immunolocalization evidence
comment: A type of microscopy evidence where antibodies are used to detect the location of molecules or other structures within cells or tissues.

term: biological system reconstruction evidence
comment: A type of curator inference that is based on a combination of experimental evidences or existing models of that system in a related species used for the reconstruction of a biological system.
